    <div class="section">
        <h2 class="section-title" onclick="toggleSection(this)">
            Email <span class="arrow">▼</span>
        </h2>
        <p class="section-info">
            The email page is created only for admins to send emails to members. The email page is accessible by clicking <u>Email</u> in the navbar.
            There is no ability for members to view the emails that have been sent on the website. They will recieve the emails in their inbox.
            <br>
            <br>
            The email page is split into four sections: <b>Individual Email</b>, <b>Active Members Email</b>, <b>Active/Inactive Members Email</b>, and <b>Calendar Email</b>.
            The <b>Individual Email</b> section allows for admins to send an email to a specific member(s) of the organization.
            The <b>Active Members Email</b> section allows for admins to send an email to all members who have their graduation date set to a future date.
            The <b>Active/Inactive Members Email</b> section allows for admins to send an email to all members who have signed up for the site (Active/Inactive).
            The <b>Calendar Email</b> section allows for admins to send an email to all active members about the upcoming events for the next week.
            <br>
            <br>
            Each section has a <u>Subject</u> field and a <u>Body</u> field. The <u>Subject</u> field is where the subject of the email is entered, and the <u>Body</u> field is where the body of the email is entered.
            Once the desired information has been entered, the email can be sent by clicking the <u>Send</u> button.
            The email will come from the the EWB President's email address.
        </p>
